// Cortex-M3 + 64 KB SRAM / 512 KB flash, plus a RAM-mapped ADC register window for
// the thin-seam ADC driver content-gate. The gate asserts the exact CR2 writes (ADON
// on enable, ADON|SWSTART on start), the table-free SMPR2/SQR3/SQR1 config the DRIVER
// computes, and the Kani-proven read-after-EOC exactly-once / single-shot property —
// on a plain memory region, deterministic, no dependence on Renode's ADC peripheral
// model (whose EOC/DR sequencing would otherwise mask a dissolve no-op).
cpu: CPU.CortexM @ sysbus
    cpuType: "cortex-m3"
    nvic: nvic
nvic: IRQControllers.NVIC @ sysbus 0xE000E000
    -> cpu@0
flash: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x0
    size: 0x80000
sram: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x20000000
    size: 0x10000
// ADC1 register window (real STM32F1 address, 0x40012400, +0x400) as plain memory —
// driver SR/CR2/SMPR/SQR/DR writes read back. Ends at 0x40012800, below USART1 at
// 0x40013800 (no overlap).
adc1: Memory.MappedMemory @ sysbus 0x40012400
    size: 0x400
usart1: UART.STM32_UART @ sysbus <0x40013800, +0x100>
    -> nvic@37
